data.description: Welcome to this South Highlands Sanctuary! This pristine property is situated on a large lot, nearly half an acre, right in the heart of historic Shreveport! It is in walking distance to dining, shopping, Norton Art Gallery and more! The back porch looks over the neighboring street, right into the historic museum's gorgeous property, which makes it feel like you are in your own little world. This home boasts two huge open-concept living rooms, 4 large bedrooms, 4 bathrooms, plus an office, a cellar, and large utility room for extra storage. Speaking of storage, the closet space offered here is absolutely abundant! Natural light beams through at all hours of the day. It has been tastefully updated, but still maintains much of the original charm. The second living space displays a custom mural, just painted in 2022, while the entry way floors and kitchen floors are also unique art pieces from decades past. When I say this property is one of a kind, it TRULY is!
